This command uses the following options:

psexec @computerlist.txt -s -d powershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "C:\path\to\your\script.ps1"


@computerlist.txt: Specifies the text file containing the list of computer names.
-s: Runs the command as the System account.
-d: Runs the command in detached mode.
powershell.exe: Specifies the command to run.
-ExecutionPolicy Bypass: Bypasses the PowerShell script execution policy to allow the script to run.
-File "C:\path\to\your\script.ps1": Specifies the path to the PowerShell script that you want to run.
